laboratory_examinations.findings: A subcentimeter hypodensity in the right hepatic lobe likely represents a sclerosed hemangioma. A subcentimeter hyperenhancing focus in the left hepatic lobe likely represents a flash filling hemangioma. The appendix is dilated up to 9 mm and fluid-filled with thickened wall and mild periappendiceal fat stranding. No appendicolith identified.
MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA (>= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.
